### Complete Worked Example: Category 6 Rural Municipality

**Municipality Profile**:
- **Category**: 6
- **Population**: 8,500 (75% rural, 25% urban center)
- **Budget**: COP 4.2 billion (92% SGP-dependent, 8% own-source)
- **Administrative structure**: Mayor, 4 secretariats (Government, Planning, Health, Social Development), 12 total professional staff
- **FARFAN diagnostic focus area**: Children and Youth Rights

**Capacity Assessment (9-dimensional)**:

| Dimension | Score | Evidence | Implication |
|-----------|-------|----------|-------------|
| Individual Analytical | Low | No staff with advanced research training; Planning Secretary is engineer, not social scientist | Require external TA for data analysis |
| Organizational Analytical | Low | No M&E system; data collection is ad-hoc; no baseline indicators for children/youth | Embed data system design in recommendations |
| Systemic Analytical | Medium | ICBF regional office 35km away; departmental statistics office responsive | Can access external expertise |
| Individual Operational | Medium | Staff execute basic procurement, budget execution 78% (acceptable) | Can implement moderate-complexity instruments |
| Organizational Operational | Low | High turnover (mayor is third in 4 years due to political instability); no written SOPs | Avoid complex multi-actor coordination |
| Systemic Operational | Medium | Functional relationship with departmental government; several active NGOs | Can establish inter-institutional agreements |
| Individual Political | Low | New administration (3 months in office); no prior child policy experience | Need quick wins to build credibility |
| Organizational Political | Medium | Active JACs, functional school parent associations | Leverage existing participation structures |
| Systemic Political | Medium | Electoral stability improving; moderate social capital; low armed actor presence | Participatory approaches feasible |

**Binding Constraints**: Organizational Analytical (no data) + Organizational Operational (high turnover, no SOPs)

**FARFAN Diagnostic Findings (Children/Youth area)**:

From 60 questions in this area:
- **78% of parents** report children under 5 do not access any early childhood development programs
- **Municipal budget allocation** to children/youth programs: COP 0 (zero) beyond mandatory school meals (SGP education)
- **Chronic malnutrition rate**: 18% (departmental avg: 12%, national avg: 10%)
- **Adolescent pregnancy rate**: 24 per 1,000 girls 15-19 (departmental: 18, national: 15)
- **School dropout rate** (grades 6-11): 15% (national: 8%)
- **No municipal-level tracking** of children in vulnerable situations (abuse, exploitation, displacement)
- **Comisaría de Familia**: 1 part-time comisaria (also serves as inspector of police), no psychologist/social worker

**Problem Tree Construction**:
EFFECTS:

Adolescent pregnancy perpetuates poverty cycles
School dropouts lack economic opportunities
Chronic malnutrition affects cognitive development and long-term health
Undetected abuse cases escalate to severe harm

CENTRAL PROBLEM:
Children and adolescents in [Municipality] lack access to integral development services and protection systems
CAUSES:

No early childhood development programs beyond school meals
No adolescent pregnancy prevention/support programs
No systematic tracking of children's nutritional status or vulnerabilities
Insufficient Comisaría de Familia capacity to respond to protection cases


**Objective Formulation**:

**Objetivo General**: "Garantizar el acceso de niñas, niños y adolescentes a servicios integrales de desarrollo y protección en [Municipality]"

**Objetivos Específicos**:
1. "Ampliar la oferta de servicios de desarrollo infantil temprano para niñas y niños menores de 5 años"
2. "Prevenir el embarazo adolescente mediante educación sexual y servicios de salud sexual y reproductiva"
3. "Establecer sistema de seguimiento nutricional y detección de vulnerabilidades en población infantil"
4. "Fortalecer la capacidad de respuesta institucional frente a casos de vulneración de derechos de niñas, niños y adolescentes"

**Instrument Selection** (calibrated to LOW organizational analytical/operational capacity):

**Objetivo Específico 1** (Early childhood):
- **Problem**: 78% of under-5s lack development programs
- **Binding constraint consideration**: Municipality cannot directly operate complex early childhood center (requires high organizational operational capacity)
- **Instrument choice**: **Organization (delegation model)** + **Treasure (co-financing)**
- **Specific instrument**: Inter-institutional agreement with ICBF to expand "Hogares Comunitarios de Bienestar" (community mother program) + municipal co-financing for nutritional supplements
- **Why this works**: ICBF provides technical model, trains community mothers, supervises quality; municipality only provides complementary resources and facilities (playing to medium systemic operational capacity)

**Objetivo Específico 2** (Adolescent pregnancy prevention):
- **Problem**: Pregnancy rate 60% above national average
- **Instrument choice**: **Information** + **Organization (co-production)** + **Procedural**
- **Specific instruments**: Life skills workshops delivered by departmental health through schools + peer educator youth group (co-production) + Youth Advisory Council to mayor (procedural, builds political capacity)
- **Why this works**: Uses existing school infrastructure; departmental health provides facilitators (low municipal operational burden); youth participation addresses political capacity deficit

**Objetivo Específico 3** (Nutritional tracking/vulnerability detection):
- **Problem**: No data systems (organizational analytical capacity binding constraint)
- **Leverage point opportunity**: Point 6 (information flows)—creating data visibility enables multiple interventions
- **Instrument choice**: **Organization** + **Information** + **External TA**
- **Specific instrument**: Agreement with ICBF for "Sistema de Información Misional" implementation + municipal data entry technician + public dashboard
- **Why this works**: Leverages national system architecture (ICBF provides it); municipality only maintains data entry (low analytical capacity demand once system designed); creates foundation for evidence-based policy

**Objetivo Específico 4** (Comisaría capacity):
- **Problem**: Part-time comisaria, no specialized staff
- **Instrument choice**: **Treasure** + **Organization**
- **Specific instrument**: Hire full-time psychologist (SGP general-purpose allocation) + protocol agreement with departmental Defensoría de Familia for complex case referrals
- **Why this works**: Addresses immediate capacity gap with direct hiring (municipality can execute); uses departmental resources for specialized interventions beyond municipal capacity

**Products and Activities** (Objective 1 example):

**Producto 1**: "Convenio interadministrativo con ICBF para ampliación de Hogares Comunitarios de Bienestar"
- **Unidad de medida**: Número de convenios
- **Meta**: 1 convenio vigente atendiendo 120 niños y niñas

**Actividades**:
1. Negociar con ICBF regional términos de ampliación, identificando 8 madres comunitarias potenciales en veredas con mayor concentración de niñez
2. Adecuar 8 viviendas comunitarias (salones comunales, casetas JAC) para cumplir estándares mínimos de ICBF mediante refacciones menores
3. Asignar presupuesto municipal para complemento nutricional (leche, frutas) y materiales didácticos no cubiertos por ICBF
4. Realizar seguimiento trimestral con visitas conjuntas ICBF-Secretaría de Desarrollo Social

**Producto 2**: "Programa de complementación nutricional para niños y niñas en Hogares Comunitarios"
- **Unidad de medida**: Número de niños beneficiados
- **Meta**: 120 niños recibiendo complemento nutricional diario

**Actividades**:
1. Contratar proveedor local de alimentos mediante proceso de mínima cuantía para suministro mensual de leche, frutas y productos de huerta
2. Capacitar a madres comunitarias en preparación de complementos según guías nutricionales de ICBF
3. Distribuir mensualmente complementos a cada Hogar Comunitario con registro de consumo

